<br>
Travelling around your neighboring zones, find out if there's a better area for you to hunt in.  As an example:  if you are an Erudite, you can travel to either Paineel or Qeynos.  Toxxulia Forest is a terrible newbie area.  If you are in Feydwer (dwarf, woodelf, highelf, gnome), experience has shown me that the trip to Freeport is worth doing for the less-crowded zones there.<br>
<br>
<br>
Oh ... and don't forget about the Soulbinders!  When you come into a new city, look for the soulbinder and get your soul bound to the new city.  You don't want to travel too far when you die! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kiya>Kiya</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Incense-burnin' Fishergirl</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/14/02 2:18:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1107.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best tip ..</span><hr size=1> Not exactly an in-game tip, but one I just found out recently (maybe from this board?) and &quot;use&quot; all the time now:<br>
